## Vue Component Structure

### Component Order

The three main blocks of a Vue component must always be in the following order: `<template>`, `<script setup>`, and `<style>`.

### Styling

Use the `lang="scss"` and `scoped` attributes on the `<style>` tag.

### Code Example

All new components should follow this structure exactly.

```vue
<template>
  <div class="mvsd-card">
    <h1 class="mvsd-card__title">{{ title }}</h1>
  </div>
</template>

<script setup>
import { defineProps } from "vue";

const props = defineProps({
  title: {
    type: String,
    default: "Default Title",
  },
});
</script>

<style scoped lang="scss">
@import "@/styles/variables.scss";

.mvsd-card {
  border: 1px solid $mvsd-color-border;
  padding: $mvsd-spacing-md;

  &__title {
    color: $mvsd-color-text-dark;
  }
}
</style>
```
